# Google Places API key — https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Free tier is plenty for this exercise.
#
# If you use the client-side Places JS library, this key is exposed to the
# browser; restrict it to your HTTP referrers in the GCP console.
# If you use a Next.js API route as a proxy, you can drop NEXT_PUBLIC_ and
# keep the key server-side only.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=
